Hello!
> that send 3 unreachables, like normal, linux does fine with.
Yes, Linux sends only 1 error message per second to each source with 
bursts up to 6 by default.
It means only that loss measurements with traceroute
are completely bogus. At least, all the routers in our neighbourhood
answer exactly ONE of three traceroute probes 8)
Alexey Kuznetsov
